{"title":"Hemorragia Digestiva Baja","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Gastroenterología/- Hemorragia Digestiva Baja-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Hemorragia\\NDigestiva Baja","guid":"cIoiPy1taVN7EszVRkE0rQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Introducción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Clasificación\\NAnatómica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Alta: Desde el esfínter esofágico superior hasta el ángulo de Treitz.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Media: Desde el ángulo de Treitz hasta el íleon distal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"2","text":"• Baja: Desde la válvula ileocecal hasta el ano.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"• Enfoque: Hemorragia digestiva baja (HDB), incluyendo causas originadas en el íleon distal, excluyendo patología periorificial y anemia crónica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"• Detención espontánea: 80%-85% de los casos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"1","text":"• Recurrencia: Hasta 25% de los pacientes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"• Mortalidad global: 2%-4%.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"0","text":"Etiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Frecuentes:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• Enfermedad diverticular: 30%-65%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"• Colitis isquémica: 4%-20%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"• Hemorroidal: 4%-20%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"11","text":"• Angiodisplasias: 4%-15%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"11","text":"• Enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal: 3%-5%.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"10","text":"• Otras:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Lesiones vasculares: Isquemia, hemorroides, angiodisplasias, inducidas por radiación.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"• Inflamatorias: Infecciones, enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"17","text":"• Neoplásicas: Polipósicas, malignas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"17","text":"• Iatrogénicas: Complicaciones endoscópicas y quirúrgicas.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"• Evaluación según edad y antecedentes clínicos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"• Factores\\Nidentificados:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• Edad avanzada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"• Uso de AINEs.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"24","text":"• Posintervenciones quirúrgicas o endoscópicas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"24","text":"• Enfermedades cardiovasculares.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"24","text":"• Isquemia intestinal.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"22","text":"• Colonoscopía: Indicación más frecuente en la evaluación del paciente con HDB.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"22","text":"• Estudios retrospectivos: Pueden no establecer con certeza la fuente directa del sangrado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"22","text":"• Detención espontánea con medidas de soporte: 70%-80% de los casos.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"Presentación\\NClínica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• Hematoquecia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"• Descripción: Evacuación de deposiciones marrón o rojo vinoso.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"• Origen: Colon derecho.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"33","text":"• Rectorragia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Descripción: Evacuación de sangre fresca, color rojo brillante.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"• Origen: Colon izquierdo o canal anal.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"40","parent":"33","text":"Variación del Aspecto y Color\\Nde las Deposiciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"• Velocidad del tránsito intestinal: Puede afectar el color y aspecto de las deposiciones.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"• HDB del\\Ncolon derecho:","guid":"Q53ZlykNR0ECRjc0LIU3ZQ","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• Tránsito acelerado: Puede presentarse como hematoquecia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"• Tránsito enlentecido: Puede presentarse como melena.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"45","parent":"40","text":"• Hemorragia digestiva alta:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"• Tránsito acelerado: Puede presentarse como hematoquecia.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"40","text":"• Estadísticas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Hematoquecia: 10%-15% de los pacientes con hematoquecia tienen una hemorragia digestiva alta.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"0","text":"Anamnesis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"• Cuantía y características de la hemorragia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"• Episodios previos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"• Síntomas asociados:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"• Cambios en el hábito intestinal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"• Baja de peso.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"52","text":"• Dolor abdominal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"52","text":"• Relación temporal con el período menstrual.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"57","parent":"49","text":"• Comorbilidades:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• Enfermedad diverticular.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"• Enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"57","text":"• Cirugías o endoscopias previas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"49","text":"• Medicamentos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"• Antiagregantes plaquetarios.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"• Anticoagulantes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"61","text":"• AINEs.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"61","text":"• Corticoides.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"66","parent":"49","text":"• Dolor abdominal: Puede sugerir origen inflamatorio, isquémico, infeccioso o perforación.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"0","text":"Examen Clínico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Estado hemodinámico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"• Inspección anal y tacto rectal:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"• Aspecto de las deposiciones (rectorragia, hematoquecia o melena).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"• Descartar masa rectal.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"0","text":"Laboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• Hemograma completo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• Grupo sanguíneo/Rh","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"• Estudios de coagulación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"• Función renal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"72","text":"• Hematocrito/hemoglobina:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"• Evaluar cada 2-12 h según gravedad del sangrado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"• Inicialmente puede no reflejar pérdidas, evidenciándose con el paso de las horas.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"72","text":"• Determinación de\\Nriesgo asociado:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"• Hematocrito/hemoglobina inicial.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"• Parámetros de estabilidad hemodinámica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"• Presencia de hemorragia persistente.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"0","text":"Imágenes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"• Angiotomografía Computada\\N(angio TAC):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"• Diagnóstico esencial en HDB.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"• Identifica sangrado activo (>0,3-0,5 ml/min).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"85","text":"• Visualiza punto sangrante y determina etiología.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"85","text":"• Sensibilidad: 85%, Especificidad: 92%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"85","text":"• Requiere radiación y medio de contraste endovenoso\\N(riesgo de nefropatía y reacciones alérgicas).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"85","text":"• Planificación de terapia endoscópica, radiológica o cirugía.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"84","text":"• Cintigrama con glóbulos rojos\\Nmarcados con isótopos radioactivos (Tc\\N99m):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"• Identifica sangrados menores e intermitentes (0,1-0,5 ml/min).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"• Poco disponible, baja precisión en localización del sitio de sangrado.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"0","text":"Manejo Terapéutico\\NMultidisciplinario","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"• Equipo: Gastroenterólogo, coloproctólogo, radiólogo intervencional.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"• Importancia: Mayor relevancia en casos de hemorragia severa y alto riesgo de complicaciones por patología concomitante.","guid":"VP533BoKLD943Lb8TuTcbw","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"0","text":"Selección y\\NTriage","guid":"M9XgjxTcG7Iggf0JbUXOLw","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"• Opciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"• Manejo ambulatorio.","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":" Pacientes de muy bajo riesgo (jóvenes, sanos, hemodinámicamente estables, sangrado escaso).","guid":"UUcHL3jI-iZQWVbicXSU8g","children":[]}]},{"id":"102","parent":"99","text":"• Hospitalización en sala.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"99","text":"• Ingreso a unidades de paciente crítico.","guid":"","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"Inestabilidad hemodinámica, sangrado persistente y/o patologías relevantes.","guid":"W5OpC0rHJT0r1lNeQfEEew","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"98","text":"Factores de Riesgo al Inicio de Presentación\\Nde la Hemorragia Digestiva Baja","guid":"I0do6G5cmuBqSg34NGFhIA","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"1. Inestabilidad hemodinámica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"2. Hto/Hb bajo < 35%/9 g/dl.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"105","text":"3. Comorbilidades.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"105","text":"4. Sangrado persistente.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"98","text":"• Factores de alto riesgo\\N(Score de Oakland):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"• Inestabilidad hemodinámica (hipotensión, taquicardia, ortostatismo, síncope).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"• Sangrado persistente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"110","text":"• Sangrado no asociado a dolor abdominal ni diarrea.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"110","text":"• Sangrado previo por divertículos o angiodisplasias.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"110","text":"• Comorbilidades significativas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"110","text":"• Edad avanzada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"110","text":"• Hospitalización por otra patología.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"110","text":"• Uso de aspirina y/o anticoagulantes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"110","text":"• Tiempo de protrombina prolongado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"110","text":"• Hipoalbuminemia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"110","text":"• Anemia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"110","text":"• Nitrógeno ureico elevado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"110","text":"• Recuento anormal de glóbulos blancos.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"0","text":"Estimación de Pérdidas y\\NEvaluación Hemodinámica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"• Estimación clínica: Basada en hemodinamia y hematocrito inicial.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"• Comorbilidades: Pueden alterar parámetros por medicamentos (antihipertensivos, b-bloqueadores, otros), y\\Npresentar complicaciones asociadas (déficit de flujo renal, isquemia miocárdica o de extremidades inferiores).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"Evaluación de Estabilidad\\NHemodinámica, Hipovolemia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"1. Taquicardia de reposo: Hipovolemia leve a moderada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"2. Hipotensión ortostática (descenso de 20 mmHg de PA sistólica y 10 mmHg de PA diastólica al pasar a posición de pie):\\NPérdida del 15% de la volemia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"127","text":"3. Hipotensión en decúbito: Pérdida del 40% de la volemia.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"0","text":"Medidas Iniciales para\\NEstabilización del Paciente","guid":"","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"1. Monitorización","guid":"","children":[{"id":"133","parent":"132","text":"• Registro cardiovascular\\Ncontinuo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"• Presión arterial.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"• Frecuencia cardíaca.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"• Saturación de oxígeno.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"132","text":"• Monitorización más profunda: En pacientes cardiópatas o comprometidos hemodinámicamente.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"131","text":"2. Oxigenación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"• Suplementación de oxígeno: Según necesidad.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"131","text":"3. Resucitación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"• Instalación de 2 vías venosas periféricas gruesas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"• Volemización por metas cardiovasculares: Con cristaloides (suero fisiológico o ringer lactato).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"131","text":"4. Transfusión de\\NHemoderivados","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"• Evaluación caso a caso: Necesidad de transfusión.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"• Transfusión restrictiva de glóbulos rojos: Mejor pronóstico.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"143","text":"• Indicaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"• Hb < 7,0 g/dl.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"• Hb < 9,0 g/dl en pacientes con comorbilidades cardiovasculares.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"131","text":"5. Corrección de\\NCoagulopatía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"• Evaluación individual: Riesgo/beneficio del uso de anticoagulantes y/o antiagregantes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"149","text":"• Suspensión y\\Nreversión de efectos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"• Vitamina K.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"• Plasma fresco congelado.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"149","text":"• Otros.","guid":"","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"• Tratamiento crítico: Conducta adoptada de acuerdo con el tratante (cardiólogo o neurólogo)\\Nen pacientes con riesgo alto de complicaciones cardiovasculares.","guid":"bEJuHCfRxkhKe0ZGXMyQWw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"156","parent":"0","text":"Hemorragia Digestiva Baja:\\NTerapia Endoscópica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"157","parent":"156","text":"Estabilización Previa del Paciente","guid":"bptaXSVT_DxFYkCYQ5nSOQ","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"• Requisito previo: Estabilización del paciente antes del estudio endoscópico.","guid":"VT8vm0WOExwjDcUIGN0JMw","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"156","text":"Evaluación de\\NHematoquecia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"• Tracto digestivo alto:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"• Hematoquecia puede originarse en el tracto digestivo alto.","guid":"P14oez4-95QSfq6pczQJCg","children":[]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"• Descartar: Presencia de coágulos en deposiciones sugiere origen bajo.","guid":"UxsTRzMAq7Jgedc6Lq68Ug","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"159","text":"• Indicaciones: Inestabilidad hemodinámica e hipotensión ortostática sugieren causa alta.","guid":"fcfQ7wxQKphwn8DOTw7YHw","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"159","text":"• Procedimiento: Realizar endoscopia alta previo a colonoscopía.","guid":"BRkkv0D5F7BAg20RKGCNpw","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"156","text":"Sonda\\NNasogástrica","guid":"bMtIKhtydhBAu3ogW2aihw","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"• Utilidad: Descarta sangrado alto.","guid":"L1WykSrNewlcwe7HG5ggrQ","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"• Preparación: Administración de laxantes previo a colonoscopía.","guid":"Up9BUic9NQ54ZLEIJ95w7Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"156","text":"Preparación para\\NColonoscopía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"• Limpieza del colon: Esencial para adecuada exploración.","guid":"QMZyTAYdurkfAHTBACSaxw","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"• Agente: Polietilenglicol (PEG) en dosis mínima necesaria.","guid":"RFyyTTF_I2pzWKPSF3fFlA","children":[]}]},{"id":"171","parent":"156","text":"Momento de la\\NColonoscopía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"• Evidencia: No hay diferencia significativa si se realiza antes de 24 h versus 24-96 h desde inicio del sangrado.","guid":"ZH_PHFPSewxGJoHnYkegDA","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"171","text":"• Requisitos: Paciente estable, adecuada preparación colónica, disponibilidad de armamentario diagnóstico/terapéutico, asistente entrenado.","guid":"YCKlpDbGQrUxVngrZTvKYw","children":[]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"156","text":"Procedimiento de\\NColonoscopía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"• Limpieza prolija: Uso de jeringas de alto volumen o bomba de lavado.","guid":"d79aZXHZ5TwNnFgLJxUM9g","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"• Exploración: Mucosa durante inserción y retiro del equipo, incluyendo íleon terminal.","guid":"HKdgRWpeRtJCrS2jb0ahlw","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"174","text":"• Soluciones de lavado: Considerar uso de enzimas; no usar agua oxigenada.","guid":"EZt74DsR3qsXJRKFfmbECg","children":[]}]},{"id":"178","parent":"156","text":"Capacidad Diagnóstica\\Ny Terapéutica","guid":"VoRUu1fgjKVZzWaSF0rHBw","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"• Preferencia: Colonoscopía con preparación adecuada.","guid":"Xf5HXnjN21MXb2HPIlr5rA","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"178","text":"• Diagnóstico: Etiología o causa potencial en 70%-90% de los pacientes.","guid":"Kkz-vQrIBaE50r9ADszN2Q","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"178","text":"• Factores: Actividad del sangrado, nivel de preparación colónica, experiencia del operador.","guid":"XpqArX_5QSdxFG3lPr0mUQ","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"178","text":"• Divertículos: Sugiere responsabilidad si son el único hallazgo.","guid":"Nr-D3CJq5hAj-PC1Ln7eQg","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"178","text":"• Alcance: Ciego en 95% de los casos, complicaciones en 2%.","guid":"FETLTDGVSMBVk-s4MOwrkg","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"156","text":"Tratamiento del\\NSitio de Sangrado","guid":"","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"• Terapia dual: Inyectoterapia (adrenalina diluida) más otro tratamiento.","guid":"G_OPkhhBGNwgMs0pLY8Lcw","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"• Opciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"• Mecánicos: Clips, macroclips.","guid":"U1L3hzdX364r9c99KddMQw","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"• Térmicos: Coagulación con argón plasma, electrocoagulación.","guid":"DzhsVAXDNg9BIhNKbTazsg","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"186","text":"• Polvos hemostáticos: Hemospray.","guid":"fpERYliRdRkPka1eKN4QHw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"156","text":"Recurrencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"• Abordaje: Manejo endoscópico nuevamente en caso de recurrencias.","guid":"Y1l6uklkbJ83qt35QfP7Zw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"0","text":"Hemorragia Digestiva Baja:\\NRadiología Intervencional","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"Angiografía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"• Indicaciones: Pacientes con HDB no estabilizados hemodinámicamente.","guid":"SV2txii_S94AsSG5AB0xow","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"• Ventajas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"• No requiere preparación intestinal.","guid":"Syox7ySqEm4unA_lX279Ow","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"195","text":"• Precisión en la anatomía vascular.","guid":"Vj9bLgQv-x0QWyjNcjLqwA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"192","text":"Procedimiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"• Inicio: A través de la arteria mesentérica superior.","guid":"HHET-TCN9fcfwfYzb8QLgQ","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"• Continuación: Si el estudio es negativo, se procede con la arteria mesentérica inferior y tronco celíaco.","guid":"Z-XVpUu3xbEZm1fEdx5B-Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"192","text":"Finalidades","guid":"","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"• Diagnóstica: Demuestra alteraciones vasculares (angiodisplasias, neocirculación).","guid":"UXr7wFq9aw5kVPWsUAwNIw","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"201","text":"• Terapéutica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"204","parent":"203","text":"• Administración de drogas vasoactivas: Vasopresina intraarterial.","guid":"M07gKHPmowp46h1CFqha4g","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"• Riesgo: Resangrado 50%, arritmias, isquemia intestinal.","guid":"PUsPqTCU-ztYnFZKBqi9cA","children":[]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"203","text":"• Embolización: Ha reemplazado la\\Ninfusión de vasoactivos.","guid":"WVRHGllNeAMGxe8TJH55CQ","children":[{"id":"207","parent":"206","text":"• Efectividad: Control del sangrado en 97% de los casos.","guid":"ffeKcTVh_vgD7XZEVDblnw","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"206","text":"• Frecuencia de efectos adversos: Menor (daño arterial,\\Ntrombos, injuria renal, isquemia intestinal).","guid":"OZH6FRRInxJGadBfVgMODw","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"206","text":"• Mejora: Canulación selectiva de\\Nvasos distales a través del\\Ntelescopaje (80% de los casos).","guid":"RNaVCWYrxpNFxxmQLLxqrg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"210","parent":"192","text":"Requisitos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"• Sangrado activo: Con flujo de 0,5-1 ml/min.","guid":"MeOMRF9icVQj2qyoA16IBA","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"210","text":"• Angio-TAC previo: Necesario para confirmar hemorragia activa.","guid":"Oh_cYggvolRTapUnbW68ig","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"210","text":"• Tiempo de acción: Realizar angiografía antes de 90 min si se demuestra hemorragia activa.","guid":"fBZFXkxUsmoEFxdtOWFVCA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"214","parent":"0","text":"Hemorragia Digestiva Baja:\\NCirugía","guid":"fOmtpVyzbbdAChJ4Vj30vw","children":[{"id":"215","parent":"214","text":"Indicaciones para Cirugía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"216","parent":"215","text":"• Casos refractarios:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"• Hemorragia persistente o recurrente.","guid":"NgDlukbQAYt6vG3IM_hwKw","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"216","text":"• Dificultad para mantener la hemodinamia.","guid":"fDIAg36p5A0IL1XKNcP6mA","children":[]},{"id":"219","parent":"216","text":"• Necesidad de politransfusión de hemoderivados.","guid":"EvKDH06ZJikLxwinV8kYKA","children":[]}]},{"id":"220","parent":"215","text":"• Recomendación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"• Intentar manejo por radiología intervencional previamente, según disponibilidad del centro hospitalario.","guid":"NMTsvFGOIjcEhYLWZqh5AA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"222","parent":"214","text":"Resultados de la Cirugía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"• Mejoría: Localización exacta del sitio de sangrado.","guid":"MPCTiyhgL35qBwEFaxBv7g","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"222","text":"• Peores resultados: Cirugía sin determinación del sitio preciso del sangrado.","guid":"MI_R0j1xlixYfyx4LKYXMQ","children":[]},{"id":"225","parent":"222","text":"• Esfuerzo previo: Búsqueda del origen del sangrado antes de proceder a la cirugía.","guid":"CcZIllyWQ-VmB2w5Bq_2PA","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":225,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Gastroenterología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Gastroenterología","filename":"- Hemorragia Digestiva Baja-2024","id":"map_637","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"- Hemorragia Digestiva Baja-2024"}